    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-01T03:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-01T03:30:00-05:00" n="148"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690B.9321/3–154: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 148<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Burma (<persName type="from"
                            >Sebald</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d148fn1">Repeated to Bangkok and Taipei.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rangoon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-01T15:00:00+06:30"
                            >March 1, 1954—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>835. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptels</gloss> 755<note n="2" xml:id="d148fn2">
                        <ref target="#d147">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> and 760.<note n="3" xml:id="d148fn3">Telegram 760, Feb. 27,
                        instructed the Embassy in Rangoon to stress to the Burmese Foreign Office
                        the importance of the Burmese agreement to the continuation of the
                        evacuation. (690B.9321/2–2754)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <item>
                        <p>Part I. Called on Permanent Secretary Foreign Office who handling <gloss
                                target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> problem. Pursuant to committee’s
                            request received February 24 through Pe Khin <gloss target="#t_GUB1"
                                >GUB</gloss> has worked out extension ceasefire in certain areas as
                            follows: <list>
                                <label>a.</label>
                                <item>Until March 15, cease-fire in area ten mile radius each Mong
                                    Hsat, Mong Kwan, Mong Yawng, Mong Yang and Pangyang.</item>
                                <label>b.</label>
                                <item>
                                    <p>Until March 15, three miles on each side road Mong Hsat-Mong
                                        Tum-Mong Kwan-Tachilek.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> Cease-fire points have been
                                        selected on theory that <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMTs</gloss>
                                        could concentrate at any one or more of points mentioned.
                                        Permanent Secretary said when troops desire proceed Mong
                                        Hsat, committee should be notified and usual arrangements
                                        for safe conduct made through Burmese liaison.</p>
                                </item>
                                <label>c.</label>
                                <item>March 16 until March 31: Mong Kwan (ten mile radius) and three
                                    miles each side road to Tachilek.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi> Permanent Secretary said above
                            cease-fire plan represents considered view <gloss target="#t_GUB1"
                                >GUB</gloss> and after March 31 question of further extension will
                            not be considered. He expressed belief above plan would be sufficient
                            facilitate evacuation those who agree evacuate.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <p>Part II. Permanent Secretary fully informed by Pe Khin re desire <gloss
                                target="#t_KMT1">KMTs</gloss> in Tenasserim evacuate. Stated no
                            objection on part <gloss target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> if <gloss
                                target="#t_KMT1">KMTs</gloss> desire leave from Myawadi or Palu, but
                            latest information from Bangkok indicates <gloss target="#t_KMT1"
                                >KMTs</gloss> themselves have chosen Palu in view confused situation
                            Myawadi.</p>
                        <p>He stated Myawadi would soon be attacked by Burma Army but should <gloss
                                target="#t_KMT1">KMTs</gloss> serve notice their desire evacuate
                            from Palu, latter place would not be attacked. Suggests however
                            evacuation be undertaken without delay in view Burma Army operations
                            against <gloss target="#t_KNDO1">KNDO</gloss>’s Tenasserim area.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>Part III. Permanent Secretary unresponsive suggestion <gloss
                            target="#t_GUB1">GUB</gloss> pay Mae Sod-Lampang airlift but agreed
                        consider. Reiterated Burmese commitment pay all expenses within
                        Burma.</item>
                    <pb facs="0223" n="203" xml:id="pg_203"/>
                    <item>Part IV. Pe Khin leaving for Bangkok March 2 with complete instructions
                        concerning cease-fire parts 1 and 2 which already telegraphed Burmese
                        Embassy Bangkok.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sebald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
